7. No-Code Migration Plan

Phase C1: Classify and Annotate Legacy Signal Objects

Goal: Establish a shared classification map so all agents know what each object is and what role it will play.

- Annotate PatternResult, SignalAttempt, SignalResult, SignalPipeline with BRC role comments (not code changes, just documentation/ADR)
- Create a classification document mapping legacy objects to target BRC roles
- Identify which SignalResult fields are "signal identity" vs "execution parameters"
- Document that SignalPipeline.signal_executor is the primary S0 finding: the execution trigger must be separated
- Deliverable: ADR or classification table in docs/canon/

Phase C2: Introduce or Clarify StrategyContractV2

Goal: Create an explicit aggregate contract object that binds strategy family identity to policy.

- Decide whether StrategyContractV2 should be a new class wrapping StrategySignalV2 + identity fields, or whether StrategySignalV2 itself should be extended with strategy_family_id, strategy_family_version_id, contract_version, trial_binding_id
- Bridge StrategyFamilySignalInput / StrategyFamilySignalOutput identity fields into the v2 contract (either via adapter enhancement or schema merge)
- Enhance PatternResultToStrategySignalV2Adapter to populate at least strategy_family_id and contract_version (currently hardcoded to StrategyFamily.PATTERN)
- Deliverable: Updated strategy_contract_v2.py with BRC identity fields; updated adapter

